  "prompt": "How can I buy lego transformers? What are the options?",
  "response": "Buying LEGO Transformers can be a bit tricky since LEGO doesn\u2019t officially produce Transformers sets. Instead, **Transformers building sets** are typically made by **Kre-O**, a building block brand owned by Hasbro, the company behind Transformers. However, there are ways to get Transformers-themed LEGO-like sets or custom builds. Here are your options:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Kre-O Transformers Sets**  \n   - Kre-O is the official building block brand for Transformers. The sets include block-based Transformer figures that can transform between robot and vehicle modes.  \n   - **Where to buy**:  \n     - Amazon  \n     - eBay (for discontinued sets)  \n     - Hasbro\u2019s official website  \n   - Examples: Kre-O Optimus Prime, Kre-O Bumblebee, and other character sets.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Third-Party LEGO-Compatible Transformers Sets**  \n   - Some third-party brands produce LEGO-compatible Transformers sets. These are unofficial but often high-quality.  \n   - **Popular brands**:  \n     - **Mega Construx** (Hasbro\u2019s other building block line, sometimes features Transformers)  \n     - **Lepin** or other brick brands (check for compatibility and quality).  \n   - **Where to buy**:  \n     - AliExpress  \n     - BrickLink  \n     - Specialty toy stores  \n\n---\n\n### 3. **Custom LEGO Transformers Builds**  \n   - LEGO enthusiasts and builders create custom Transformers designs using standard LEGO bricks. You can find instructions or pre-made custom kits online.  \n   - **Options**:  \n     - **Rebrickable** (search for Transformers MOCs \u2013 My Own Creations)  \n     - **eBay** (custom kits or completed builds)  \n     - **Etsy** (custom Transformers LEGO sets)  \n     - **YouTube** (tutorials to build your own)  \n\n---\n\n### 4. **LEGO-Compatible Transformers Minifigures**  \n   - Some sellers create custom LEGO-compatible minifigures of Transformers characters. These are great for collectors.  \n   - **Where to buy**:  \n     - eBay  \n     - Etsy  \n     - BrickLink  \n\n---\n\n### 5. **LEGO Ideas \u2014 Fan Submissions**  \n   - Keep an eye on **LEGO Ideas**, a platform where fans submit designs for LEGO sets. Occasionally, Transformers-themed submissions appear, though none have been officially produced yet.  \n\n---\n\n### Tips:  \n- **Check compatibility**: If buying third-party bricks, ensure they\u2019re compatible with LEGO.  \n- **Research sellers**: For custom builds or discontinued sets, verify seller reviews.  \n- **Build your own**: If you\u2019re creative, design your own Transformers using LEGO bricks!  \n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like recommendations for specific sets or sellers! \ud83e\udd16\ud83e\uddbe",
